---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="PC System Requirements"
  description="Official Ace Combat 8 PC requirements: Windows 11, i7-10700K or Ryzen 5 3600X, 16GB RAM, RTX 2060 or RX 6600 XT, SSD and 125GB storage."
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'System Requirements' }]} />
  <article class="container article">
    <span class="eyebrow">PC (Steam) — confirmed by Bandai Namco</span>
    <h1>System Requirements</h1>

    <div class="card callout">
      <p class="mono eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Hard requirements — not optional</p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        Wings of Theve requires an <strong>SSD</strong>, a <strong>hardware ray
        tracing-capable graphics card</strong>, and <strong>DirectX 12 with Shader Model 6.6
        or higher</strong>. If your GPU doesn't support hardware ray tracing, the game will not
        run regardless of your other specs — this isn't a "recommended" setting you can turn
        off.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Official minimum PC specifications</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="dossier-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>OS</th><td>Windows 11, 64-bit</td></tr>
          <tr><th>CPU</th><td>Intel Core i7-10700K or AMD Ryzen 5 3600X</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Memory</th><td>16 GB RAM</td></tr>
          <tr><th>GPU</th><td>NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2060 6 GB or AMD Radeon RX 6600 XT 8 GB</td></tr>
          <tr><th>DirectX</th><td>Version 12, Shader Model 6.6+</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Storage</th><td>125 GB available space on an SSD</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Target</th><td>1080p upscaled / 30 fps / Low; drops possible in intensive scenes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Baseline performance target</h2>
    <p>
      Bandai Namco's own estimate for minimum-spec hardware is <strong>1080p with upscaling
      at roughly 30fps on "Low" graphics settings</strong>, with framerate expected to drop
      further in graphics-intensive scenes (large-scale battles, superweapon encounters). This
      is a performance-mode baseline, not a locked 30fps guarantee.
    </p>

    <h2>What this means if you're upgrading</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Any GPU older than the ray-tracing generation (pre-RTX 20-series / pre-RX 6000-series equivalents) won't be able to launch the game at all.</li>
      <li>A SATA HDD is not sufficient — the SSD requirement is almost certainly tied to the "Cloudly" weather/streaming system needing fast asset loading for its multi-layered cloud rendering.</li>
      <li>Shader Model 6.6 support generally lines up with DirectX 12 Ultimate-capable GPUs — if your card supports DX12U, you likely clear this bar.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="card callout">
      <p class="mono eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">Still unconfirmed</p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        Steam has published the minimum table above, but the recommended CPU, GPU, memory and
        performance target are still listed as TBD. Do not treat a third-party “recommended
        build” as an official specification.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedLinks items={[
    { href: '/release-date', label: 'Release Date & Platforms', desc: 'When and where you can play, on every platform.' },
    { href: '/editions', label: 'Editions Compared', desc: 'Standard vs Deluxe vs Joker Flight Pack.' },
  ]} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article { padding: 56px 0 80px; max-width: 720px; }
  .article p, .article li { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .article ul { padding-left: 20px; }
  .article li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .callout { margin: 24px 0; }
  .table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin: 24px 0 32px; }
</style>
